title: Static Analysis

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

com.google.android.c2dm.permission.RECEI.description: Permission for cloud to device messaging.

android.permission.RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETE.description: Allows an application to start itself as soon as the system has finished booting. This can make it take longer to start the phone and allow the application to slow down the overall phone by always running.

android.permission.FOREGROUND_SERVICE.description: Allows a regular application to use Service.startForeground

manifest_analysis.title:
App has a Network Security Configuration
[android:networkSecurityConfig=@xml/network_security_config]
manifest_analysis.desc: The Network Security Configuration feature lets apps customize their network security settings in a safe, declarative configuration file without modifying app code. These settings can be configured for specific domains and for a specific app.
manifest_analysis.name: App has a Network Security Configuration [android:networkSecurityConfig]

manifest_analysis.title: Launch Mode of Activity (com.accointing.MainActivity) is not standard.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask/singleInstance" as it becomes root Activity and it is possible for other applications to read the contents of the calling Intent. So it is required to use the "standard" launch mode attribute when sensitive information is included in an Intent.
manifest_analysis.name: Launch Mode of Activity is not standard.

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has full RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In Full RELRO, the entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) is marked as read-only.

rpath.description: The shared object does not have run-time search path or RPATH set.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

playstore_details.title: Accointing – Crypto Tracker
playstore_details.description:
Welcome to the ACCOINTING.COM Crypto-Tracker, your next-generation crypto portfolio tracking app. Track the latest live cryptocurrency prices with real-time data, review key market trends in a glimpse, and review all your trades and transactions and let the app calculate your actual profit. 


Supported exchanges: Coinbase, Binance, Kraken, OKEX, Binance DEX, Bibox, Deribit, Bitcoin.de, Bitpanda, Bitfinex, Bittrex, Bitstamp, IDEX, Kucoin, Gemini, Poloniex, Btcmarkets, Hitbtc, and more via direct API connection.

Supported wallets/blockchains: Bitcoin, Ethereum, Litecoin, Polkadot, Binance Smart Chain, Chainlink, Ledger and more via direct address connection.


Manual data entry also available as well as support for more than 6,000 different altcoins. Stop using spreadsheets and don't let the bull catch you off-guard. Start tracking like a pro today.


FEATURES:


• Watchlist:
Keep a close track of cryptocurrencies that you may want to invest and trade. Receive relevant information such as price change over time, percentage change over time and much more.


• Market view:
Get a cryptocurrency snapshot of the whole crypto market as well as be able to look into any of the thousands of different coins on the market. Review the 24h change in price (open, close, high, low, and average price), total supply, market volume, circulating supply as well as a historical view per day, week, 3 months, 6 months and year.


• Portfolio overview:
Understand your crypto portfolio at a glance. Gains, percentage change, historical buys and sells, all for your entire portfolio or for each individual cryptocurrency. Get real-time data of your overall performance all synched with your APIs and public wallet addresses so you can create a tax report when needed.


• 24H Market Review:
Get 24-hour updates of the current market performance: total market cap, total volume, BTC dominance, open call, close call, high call, low call, 


• Price Alerts:
Set up your price alerts for your favorite tokens and be able to react when your desired price has been reached.


• Portfolio Alerts:
Portfolio fluctuation alerts as well as market feel alert (is the market bullish or bearish in the last 24h)



NOTE: The ACCOINTING.COM app does not allow crypto trading or gambling. Rather your portfolio from other sources is imported and analyzed.
